com.mojang.datafixers.optics.profunctors

Interface Profunctor<P extends K2,Mu extends Profunctor _>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - The container type.
    Mu - The witness type for this profunctor.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Mu<P>, Kind2 P
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AffineP<P,Mu>, Cartesian<P,Mu>, Closed<P,Mu>, Cocartesian<P,Mu>, GetterP<P,Mu>, Mapping<P,Mu>, Monoidal<P,Mu>, MonoidProfunctor<P,Mu>, ReCartesian<P,Mu>, ReCocartesian<P,Mu>, TraversalP<P,Mu>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Adapter.Instance, Affine.Instance, Forget.Instance, ForgetOpt.Instance, FunctionType.Instance, Lens.Instance, Prism.Instance, ProfunctorFunctorWrapper.Instance, ReForgetC.Instance, Traversal.Instance

    public interface Profunctor<P extends K2,Mu extends Profunctor _>
extends Kind2 P
    The profunctor type class defines a method, dimap(Function, Function), which transforms a mapping between types to a mapping between wrapped types.

    This type class requires that the container P is contravariant in its first parameter.

    Type Shape:
    %.Type. %0
    See Also:
    Understanding profunctors

    • Method Detail

      • dimap

        <A,B,C,D> (P<A,B>) -> P<C,D> dimap((C) -> A g,
                                   (B) -> D h)
        Takes a function from the output type C to the input type A and a function from the input type B to the output type D, and returns a function from a container of A, B to a container of C, D.

        A straightforward example of an implementation of dimap is the method Function.andThen(Function). For functions, the expression 

        
 dimap(g, h).apply(f)

        is equivalent to 

        
 g.andThen(f).andThen(h)
        Type Parameters:
        A - The first input type.
        B - The second input type.
        C - The first output type.
        D - The second output type.
        Parameters:
        g - A function from output to input.
        h - A function from input to output.
        Returns:
        A function from an input container to an output container.
        See Also:
        dimap(App2, Function, Function)

                               (C) -> A g,
